text: The National Assembly (, , ) is one of the two houses (chambers) of the Parliament of Cambodia. It is referred to as the lower house, with the Senate being referred to as the upper house. The National Assembly is an elected body consisting of 125 members known as Members of Parliament (MPs). Members are elected for five-year terms. ==Other websites== *National Assembly Homepage (in Khmer) *National Assembly of the Kingdom of Cambodia * EU Election Observation Mission to Cambodia - 2003 Category:Organisations based in Cambodia
